address: Paseo Prado 8, 28014 Madrid Spain
description: The Thyssen-Bornemisza Museum offers visitors an overview of art from the 13th century to the late 20th century. In the nearly one thousand works on display, visitors can contemplate the major periods and pictorial schools of western art such as the Renaissance, Mannerism, the Baroque, Rococo, Romanticism and the art of the 19th and 20th centuries up to Pop Art. The museum also features works from some movements not represented in state-owned collections, such as Impressionism, Fauvism, German Expressionism and the experimental avant-garde movements of the early 20th century. In addition, it boasts an important collection of 19th-century American painting not found in any other European museum institutions. Permanent collection hours: Tuesday to Sunday: 10.00 to 19.00 Monday: 12.00 - 16.00* *Free entry with the sponsorship of Mastercard.
name: Museo Nacional Thyssen-Bornemisza

address: Calle Prim 11 bajo Palacio Tejada, 26200 Haro Spain
description: Bodegas Manzanos Haro was founded in 1801. It is the oldest winery of the city of Haro, located in the heart of appellation Rioja. It is the only winery of that time with a vertical design that continues working. The underground tunnels of the winery are located in the old galleries of Haro´s old castle, which have been preserved since the Middle Ages. The experience we offer consist in visit of the old winery recovered and part converted into a wine museum. Tour of all the steps that our grapes follow from the vineyard to become magnificent wines. These include the 5 underground floors of its design by gravity. From the reception area through the current production area, to the bottle rack, where the magnificent XIX century aging room and the bottle crypt of the XV century stand out. Finalizing the visit in the tasting room where we will taste 7 of our best wines with an aperitif.
name: Bodegas Manzanos Haro

description: Upon arrival to Son Sant Joan International Airport at the island of Majorca, the visitor might feel uneasy due to the general lack of English support and messy arrangement of a building originally opened to the public in the midst of the past century, and subject to successive expansions which resulted in a, arguably, mazy layout. Besides the frequent signs offering directions to branching bus pick-up locations, it is highly encouraged, specially for the novel traveler, to avoid public transport (which requires knowledge of the Spanish language and being familiar with locations in order to request stops), and heading to the main entrance were Taxi Majorca cars are stationed. Taxi Majorca is an official private transport service operating for years in the island, allowing for easy Majorca airport transfers for foreigners, independently of it being from the airport to the nearby city of Palma de Mallorca, neigbouring towns or holiday resorts; or viceversa. Our customers enjoy new cars, adequately conditioned to maximize passenger comfort, a professional driver, and a clean and fast service, extremely time efficient. Stop wasting time in your transfer PMI airport using scheduled buses with low availability and low accessibility to the visitors, and allow us to excel at what we do becoming a client of us. Our company does not only supply quick Majorca airport transfers, since our company was created customers can request a taxi tour around the city. It is possible to visit the most iconic locations in the metropolis with a fairly cheap fare. Enjoying the urban sights from the comfort of our car seats is one of the best to catch a quick glimpse of the area. This choice is great for planning purposes and for those visitors who have limited time in the city. You can suggest your own route or ask our drivers for a preset taxi tour which will get you to the main points: Palma de Mallorca cathedral, Bellver castle, the coastal walkway, the old town, the Real Palace of Almudena, the old market place of gothic architecture known as Sa Llotja, the town hall, and much more. We are certain that you will enjoy the ride. Please, note that you can call your taxi from your hotel in order to get a transfer PMI airport at the end of your stay in the island. Request an appointment and a car will be waiting for you at the agreed time and date in from of your hotel door in order to pick you up, help with your luggage and drive you to the Palma de Mallorca International Airport departure gate without mishap. For further information on our services and for appointments, please check the contact information we provide.
